I just checked it. It was added by my save action plugin. I have only a very few of its action enabled, but as written that I really like having paranthesis for blocks.
[edit 2]
For example this blocks is more readable to me with paranethesis as the exception and the combined break out of the function is more visible:
			if (!hasNext())
				throw new NoSuchElementException();
			repetitionsSoFar++;
			return new RepeatFailedTestInvocationContext();

to
			if (!hasNext())` {
				throw new NoSuchElementException();
                        }
			repetitionsSoFar++;
			return new RepeatFailedTestInvocationContext();

[/edit2]
But as wished I disabled it to revert this one. So now at this if the paranthesis are gone again, but in a similar block a few lines below they are still there so we have an inconsistency there now (which I never had touched, so they are from the original author). [edit: I reverted all those changes I made /edit]
So you see were this ends? We should either define if we want to force using paranthesis or not for blocks and force them by a rule or we don't force the one or the other and let the authors use their personal like.

